<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Box Model Example</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <style>
        /* Internal CSS for the Box Model Example */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }

        .box {
            width: 300px; /* Width of the content area */
            margin: 20px auto; /* Centering the box horizontally */
            padding: 20px; /* Padding inside the box */
            border: 5px solid #4CAF50; /* Border around the box */
            background-color: #ffffff; /* Background color of the content area */
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); /* Optional shadow for depth */
        }

        .box p {
            margin: 0; /* Remove default margin for paragraph */
        }

        .explanation {
            margin-top: 20px;
            background-color: #e8f5e9; /* Light green background for explanation */
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Understanding CSS Box Model</h1>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Box Model Example</h2>
        <p>This box demonstrates the CSS box model.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation">
        <h3>Box Model Breakdown:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Content:</strong> The actual content of the box (text, images, etc.).</li>
            <li><strong>Padding:</strong> Space between the content and the border.</li>
            <li><strong>Border:</strong> The line surrounding the padding (optional).</li>
            <li><strong>Margin:</strong> Space outside the border (separates the box from other elements).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
